TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Contingency View of Porter's “Generic Strategies”
AU  - Murray, Alan I.
Y1  - 1988/07/01
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1988.4306951
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1988.4306951
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 390
EP  - 400
VL  - 13
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - According to Porter, cost leadership and product differentiation can be pursued simultaneously only under rare conditions: It is also unclear how these strategies can be implemented. In this article Porter's generic strategies are linked to external preconditions. This approach shows that the generic strategies are not mutually exclusive and that each strategy may be linked to a variety of strategic means. The implications that these results have for structuring organizations are discussed.
AB  - According to Porter, cost leadership and product differentiation can be pursued simultaneously only under rare conditions: It is also unclear how these strategies can be implemented. In this article Porter's generic strategies are linked to external preconditions. This approach shows that the generic strategies are not mutually exclusive and that each strategy may be linked to a variety of strategic means. The implications that these results have for structuring organizations are discussed.
