N2  - The article presents a commentary on the article ?The Concept of Ideology in Organizational Analysis: The Sociology of Knowledge or the Social Psychology of Beliefs',? by Richard M. Weiss and G. A. Miller. The author contends that the study mischaracterized the concept of ideology within the social sciences context. The authors explain that ideologies are sets of ideas that evolve out of specific social contexts.
AB  - The article presents a commentary on the article ?The Concept of Ideology in Organizational Analysis: The Sociology of Knowledge or the Social Psychology of Beliefs',? by Richard M. Weiss and G. A. Miller. The author contends that the study mischaracterized the concept of ideology within the social sciences context. The authors explain that ideologies are sets of ideas that evolve out of specific social contexts.
